Package eu.advance.logistics.flow.engine.block.streaming

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AppendCollection
    Returns a new collection with the given value appended to its end Signature: AppendCollection(collection, t) -> collection
    AppendMap
    Returns a new map with the given key-value pair added to the map Signature: AppendMap(map, t, u) ->map
    BufferWithSize
    Buffers the incoming values into a collection with a maximum size and forwards this collection once fully filled.
    BufferWithTime
    Buffers the incoming values into a collection within the given time window.
    ConcatCollection
    Concatenate two collections.
    ConcatMap
    Concatenate two maps.
    IsEmptyCollection
    Checks if the collection is empty.
    IsEmptyMap
    Checks if the map is empty.
    Merge
    Merges two streams of values and emits each value one after another Signature: Merge(t, t) -> t
    RelayIfTriggered
    Relay a single given value only if the trigger value has arrived.
    RemoveEntry
    Remove the given key and value pair from the map and return the new map.
    RemoveIndex
    Remove the indexth element from the collection.
    RemoveIndexRange
    Remove a range from the source collection and return two new collections, one without the elements of the range, another with the elements of the range.
    RemoveItem
    Removes the given value from the input collection and return a new collection with the number of items removed.
    RemoveKey
    Removes the given key from the map and returns a new map without that key and the value it contained Signature: RemoveKey(map, t) -> (map, u)
    RemoveValue
    Removes all the elements equal to the supplied value and returns a new map without them, plus a collection of keys which had the specified value.
    Reverse
    Reverses the element order within the collection Signature: Reverse(collection) -> collection
    SplitEven
    Split the collection into the given number of sub-collections evenly.
    SplitSize
    Split the source collection into equally sized sub-collections.
